# Dean Wiki Pipeline Rules

## Project Overview
This is a self-updating AI knowledge wiki. The pipeline ingests 
sources, filters them through a signal threshold, and writes 
synthesized Markdown pages to wiki/.

## Code Style
- Python 3.13
- Use uv for dependency management (not pip)
- All scripts must be runnable standalone AND importable as modules
- Use environment variables for all secrets — never hardcode
- Use pathlib.Path, not os.path
- Type hints on all functions
- Docstrings on all public functions

## File Conventions
- Wiki pages live in `wiki/technical/`, `wiki/world/`, and `wiki/overview.md` only
- Source cache files go to ../dean-wiki-private/sources/ — never 
  commit raw source content to this repo
- Prompt templates are Markdown files in pipeline/prompts/
- All scripts log to stdout with timestamps

## Pipeline Conventions
- Every script prints a summary at the end: files processed, 
  files written, files skipped
- Scripts exit with code 1 on failure, 0 on success
- Triage threshold is 7/10 — do not change without updating 
  pipeline/prompts/triage.md to match
- Always load Dean-Profile.md before any Claude API call that 
  writes wiki content

## Claude API Usage
- Model: claude-sonnet-4-5 for triage and updates
- Model: claude-opus-4 for weekly synthesis only
- Max tokens: 4096 for triage, 8192 for updates
- Always include Dean-Profile.md content in system prompt context
- Parse --- FILE: path/to/file.md --- blocks from responses

## What Not To Do
- Do not write files outside wiki/, pipeline/, or .github/
- Do not modify CHANGELOG.md manually — update_index.py owns it
- Do not commit anything from ../dean-wiki-private/
- Do not add dependencies without adding them to pyproject.toml and refreshing uv.lock
- Do not make Claude API calls without the Dean-Profile context